Three Cargoes to Be Dropped From North Sea Forties Plan for May

-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 
2011-05-03T16:52:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/three-cargoes-to-be-dropped-from-north-sea-forties-plan-for-may.html
Three cargoes of North Sea Forties
crude were dropped from the loading program for May, three
traders who participate in the market said today.  Shipments originally planned for three-day loading periods
starting May 14, May 24, May 30 were dropped, bringing the total
number of cargoes this month to 24, according to the people with
knowledge of the trades who asked not to be identified because
the information is confidential.  Robert Wine , a London-based spokesman for BP Plc, declined
to comment, citing company policy. BP operates the Forties
Pipeline System.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sherry Su in  London  at   lsu23@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net . 